result.execSummary:
The defendant Rachel Elizabeth Hutcheson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Rachel Elizabeth Hutcheson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Rachel Elizabeth Hutcheson was found guilty of Take/Drive Veh. w/o Consent-Abandon Veh., a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3m).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court orders time served with credit and good time calculation.

01:52 PM Defendant Rachel Elizabeth Hutcheson in court with attorney Philip A. Helgeson.  Defendant Rachel Elizabeth Hutcheson in custody from the Pierce County Jail.  Kaley Walker appeared for the State of Wisconsin. ADA Walker: guilty to Ct#2 with court costs ($443) and 67 days jail, time served. Dismiss Ct#2.  Atty Helgeson and Def agree.   Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def. Court informs Defendant of charges, possible penalties and constitutional rights.  Defendant understands charges, penalties and constitutional rights. Defendant pleas guilty to Ct#2. Counsel stipulates factual basis for the plea.   Court finds def is making plea knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily and waives constitutional rights. Court finds a factual basis to accept the plea. Court finds Defendant guilty to Ct#2 and Dismisses Ct#1. ADA Walker and Atty Helgeson address sentencing - joint recommendation. Victim addresses the court. Court orders court costs ($443) due in 9 months, DNA sample, and 67 days jail- credit for time serve with good time calculation.   Appeal rights are given to the defendant.
